<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Typing on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/typing/</link><description>Recent content in Typing on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/typing/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Mac Keyboard Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-keyboard-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/macos/macos-keyboard-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="mac-keyboard-error-fix"&gt;Mac Keyboard Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keyboard errors include keys not responding, double-typing, wrong characters appearing, sticky keys, or keyboard backlight not working.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mac keyboards use a USB HID driver. Software issues can be resolved by resetting preferences or SMC; hardware issues (liquid damage, debris) may require physical cleaning or service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Debris or liquid under keys&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Corrupt keyboard preference file&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SMC not managing keyboard properly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;macOS keyboard layout mismatch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Third-party keyboard driver conflict&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-keyboard-settings"&gt;1. Check keyboard settings&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# View current keyboard settings&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;defaults read com.apple.keyboard
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Reset keyboard preferences&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;defaults delete com.apple.keyboard
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-test-individual-keys"&gt;2. Test individual keys&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Open Keyboard Viewer&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# System Preferences → Keyboard → Input Sources → Show Input Menu in Menu Bar&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Click the input menu icon → Show Keyboard Viewer&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Press each key to identify non-responsive ones&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-clean-the-keyboard"&gt;3. Clean the keyboard&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Shut down the Mac&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Hold the Mac at a 75-degree angle&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Use compressed air in a sweeping motion across the keyboard&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Rotate and repeat for the other side&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-reset-the-smc"&gt;4. Reset the SMC&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Intel MacBooks: Shift+Control+Option+Power for 10 sec&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Apple Silicon: Shut down → Hold power for 10 sec&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# This resets keyboard hardware management&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-trackpad-error"&gt;Trackpad Error&lt;/a&gt; — pointing device issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-touchbar-error"&gt;Touch Bar Error&lt;/a&gt; — Touch Bar malfunctions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="macos-touch-id-error"&gt;Touch ID Error&lt;/a&gt; — biometric sensor issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] PHP DNF Type Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/php/php-disjunctive-normal-form/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/php/php-disjunctive-normal-form/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="php-dnf-type-error"&gt;PHP DNF Type Error&lt;/h1&gt;
